GdpPipeline create, update, and delete are
work-request-backed. The runtime records the
opening opc-work-request-id, polls
GetGdpWorkRequest through the generatedruntime
async seam, and rereads GetGdpPipeline before
projecting status or completing delete
confirmation.
GDP work-request OperationStatus values
normalize into the shared async classes and GDP
operation types normalize into create, update,
and delete phases. Raw work-request status,
operation type, message, percent complete, and
work-request ID remain visible in
status.async.current for debugging.
Success states are explicit: ACTIVE and INACTIVE
settle success, while NEEDS_ATTENTION is
terminal non-success rather than a default
active state.
Pre-create reuse is exact on compartmentId,
displayName, pipelineType, and peeringRegion,
and the runtime confirms bucketDetails from a
follow-up GET before binding to an existing
pipeline. When a tracked OCID already exists,
list reuse stays keyed to the service-specific
gdpPipelineId filter.
Mutable drift is limited to
UpdateGdpPipelineDetails fields displayName,
description, serviceLogGroupId, fileTypes,
authorizationDetails,
isFileOverrideInDestinationEnabled,
isScanningEnabled, isChunkingEnabled,
isApprovalNeeded, approvalKeyVaultId,
freeformTags, and definedTags. Strings, maps,
and false booleans keep explicit clear intent,
while zero-length fileTypes clears remain
unpublished because the pinned SDK update
request omits empty slices.
Start/Stop/Peer/Rotate/ChangeCompartment
auxiliaries remain out-of-scope drift for the
published contract.
end note
